This is the RAMSES parameter file for the non-equilibrium cooling module test.
It is a 2D run with 2*2 (i.e. four) cells, without a UV background, and hydro-static
so there is no flow between the cells and the only evolution is therefore the radiative
cooling in each cell.

&RUN_PARAMS
hydro=.true.
static_gas=.true.
ncontrol=50000
/

&AMR_PARAMS
levelmin=1
levelmax=1
ngridmax=100
boxlen=1
/

&HYDRO_PARAMS
gamma=1.666667
courant_factor=0.8
/

&INIT_PARAMS
nregion=1
region_type='square'
x_center=0.5
y_center=0.5
length_x=1.0
length_y=1.0
exp_region=10
d_region=3d0
p_region=78.282 ! 3e3 K
/

&OUTPUT_PARAMS
tout = 0.0003
/

&UNITS_PARAMS
units_density=2.18492d-24 ! 1 H/cc
units_time=3.156d13       ! 1 Myr
units_length=3.0857d18    ! 1 pc
/

&COOLING_PARAMS
cooling=.true.
neq_chem=.true.
z_ave=0.0
/

&RT_PARAMS
isHe=.true.
isH2=.true.
rt_is_init_xion=.true.
/
